H0.text: Which county won the 2013 Cricket County Championship. Yorkshire

H1.text: Which county won the 2013 Cricket County Championship. Warwickshire

H2.text: Which county won the 2013 Cricket County Championship. Middlesex

H3.text: Which county won the 2013 Cricket County Championship. Durham

A4.text: The team's most recent Championship title was in 2015.

A5.text: For the 2013 season they were called the Yorkshire Vikings.

A6.text: In the County Championship, they compete in Division One (the top division), and last won it outright in 2021 (for a total of eight championship wins).

A7.text: After the season, Warwickshire changed their name to Birmingham Bears for T20 competitions.

A8.text: In September 2013 Durham won the County Championship for a third time after beating Nottinghamshire by eight wickets at Chester le Street.

A9.text: Durham won the County Championship in 2008, retained the trophy in the 2009 season, and then won it for a third time in 2013.
